sts on three pillars: a reconceptualization of sensibility as a function of life, rather than as a primarily cognitive faculty; a focus on habits, understood as pervasive features of human behaviors acquired by attuning to the social environment; and an interpretation of human experience as "enlanguaged," namely as contingently yet irreversibly embedded in a linguistic environment that has important loop effects on human sensibility and habitual conduct.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aPhilosophy. 0aPragmatism. 0aPsychology. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Pragmatism. 4aPsychology : Psychology. 4aSociology : Sociology. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Pragmatism.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2022z978311149185140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848823340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438488233423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438488233/original  a978-3-11-149185-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles